==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Heckerism
<hw>Heck"er*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>
<sd>(a)</sd> <def>The teaching of <person>Isaac Thomas
<etsep>Hecker</etsep></person> (1819-88), which interprets Catholicism
as promoting human aspirations after liberty and truth, and as the
religion best suited to the character and institutions of the American
people.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Improperly, certain views or principles
erroneously ascribed to <person>Father Hecker</person> in a French
translation of Elliott's Life of <persfn>Hecker</persfn>. They were
condemned as ⟦ldquo⟧Americanism⟦rdquo⟧ by the Pope, in a letter to
<person>Cardinal Gibbons</person>, January 22, 1899.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Heckimal</ent>⟦br⟧
